    {
      "id": "39f8433ff85a156d27d91859796f5e50cde358b1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-11-27 21:29:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nAs I mentioned in LU-11706, I think \"experimental\" features is far too broad a bucket to put multiple features into.  The only thing I could imagine being useful is if there was a mask that filtered the OBD_CONNECT_\\* features from being enabled by a client or server.\n\nHaving a separate per-feature enable/disable tunable (e.g. mdt.*.enable_remote_dir, mdt.*.enable_striped_dir, lod.*.dom_stripesize, mdt.*.dom_read_open, osd-ldiskfs.*.auto_scrub, etc.) allows enabling/disabling a specific feature for testing, and even long after the feature is no longer considered \"experimental\" it may be useful to disable it in the field if there is some problem found with it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "13a8bf12e5117d3658957cfa7b3b3b4b082ff87c",
